'''Acclivity''', ''<code>[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]</code>''; ''[[pl (source)|pl]].'' '''Acclivities''' (&?;). [L. ''acclivitas'', fr. ''acclivis'', ''acclivus'', ascending; ''ad'' + ''clivus'' a hill, slope, fr. root ''kli'' to lean. See [[Lean]].]

A slope or inclination of the earth, as the side of a hill, considered as ''ascending'', in opposition to ''declivity'', or ''descending''; an upward slope; [[ascent]].